{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 🚀 Simulación de Predicciones y Monitoreo\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📋 Objetivos\n",
        "\n",
        "En este notebook vamos a:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. ✅ **Smoke Test**: Verificar conectividad con todos los servicios\n",
        "2. 📊 **Simulación**: Enviar 50 predicciones al Iris API\n",
        "3. 📈 **Monitoreo**: Registrar métricas en MLflow\n",
        "4. 🔍 **Drift Detection**: Generar reporte en Evidently\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🌐 Servicios disponibles\n",
        "\n",
        "Dentro del clúster de Kubernetes, los servicios se comunican por DNS:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Servicio | URL Interna | Puerto |\n",
        "|----------|-------------|--------|\n",
        "| MLflow | `http://mlflow-service:5000` | 5000 |\n",
        "| Evidently | `http://evidently-service:8000` | 8000 |\n",
        "| Iris API | `http://iris-service:8000` | 8000 |\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📦 Imports y Configuración\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import requests\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
        "import mlflow\n",
        "from evidently.report import Report\n",
        "from evidently.metric_preset import DataQualityPreset, DataDriftPreset\n",
        "import time\n",
        "from datetime import datetime\n",
        "import warnings\n",
        "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Librerías importadas correctamente\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Configuración de servicios\n",
        "MLFLOW_URI = \"http://mlflow-service:5000\"\n",
        "EVIDENTLY_URI = \"http://evidently-service:8000\"\n",
        "IRIS_API_URI = \"http://iris-service:8000\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Configurar MLflow\n",
        "mlflow.set_tracking_uri(MLFLOW_URI)\n",
        "mlflow.set_experiment(\"iris-predictions\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"🔧 MLflow URI: {MLFLOW_URI}\")\n",
        "print(f\"🔧 Evidently URI: {EVIDENTLY_URI}\")\n",
        "print(f\"🔧 Iris API URI: {IRIS_API_URI}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 🧪 1. Smoke Test - Verificar Conectividad\n",
        "\n",
        "Antes de iniciar la simulación, verificamos que todos los servicios estén respondiendo.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Test 1: MLflow\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    response = requests.get(f\"{MLFLOW_URI}/health\", timeout=5)\n",
        "    if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "        print(\"✅ MLflow está respondiendo\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"⚠️  MLflow respondió con código {response.status_code}\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"❌ Error conectando a MLflow: {e}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Test 2: Iris API\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    response = requests.get(f\"{IRIS_API_URI}/health\", timeout=5)\n",
        "    if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "        data = response.json()\n",
        "        print(f\"✅ Iris API está respondiendo\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Modelo cargado: {data.get('model_loaded', False)}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Versión: {data.get('model_version', 'unknown')}\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"⚠️  Iris API respondió con código {response.status_code}\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"❌ Error conectando a Iris API: {e}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Test 3: Información del modelo\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    response = requests.get(f\"{IRIS_API_URI}/info\", timeout=5)\n",
        "    if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "        info = response.json()\n",
        "        print(\"📊 Información del modelo:\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Tipo: {info.get('model_type', 'unknown')}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Versión: {info.get('version', 'unknown')}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Accuracy: {info.get('accuracy', 0):.4f}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Features: {info.get('feature_names', [])}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Clases: {info.get('target_names', [])}\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"❌ Error obteniendo info del modelo: {e}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Test 4: Predicción de prueba\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    test_data = {\n",
        "        \"sepal_length\": 5.1,\n",
        "        \"sepal_width\": 3.5,\n",
        "        \"petal_length\": 1.4,\n",
        "        \"petal_width\": 0.2\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    \n",
        "    response = requests.post(\n",
        "        f\"{IRIS_API_URI}/predict\",\n",
        "        json=test_data,\n",
        "        timeout=5\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "        result = response.json()\n",
        "        print(\"✅ Predicción de prueba exitosa:\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Clase predicha: {result['prediction_label']}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Confianza: {result['confidence']:.4f}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"   Probabilidades: {result['probabilities']}\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"⚠️  Error en predicción: {response.status_code}\")\n",
        "        print(response.text)\n",
        "        \n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"❌ Error en predicción de prueba: {e}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📊 2. Cargar Dataset de Referencia\n",
        "\n",
        "Cargamos el dataset Iris completo para usar como referencia y para simular predicciones.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Cargar dataset\n",
        "iris = load_iris()\n",
        "feature_names = ['sepal_length', 'sepal_width', 'petal_length', 'petal_width']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear DataFrame\n",
        "df_reference = pd.DataFrame(iris.data, columns=feature_names)\n",
        "df_reference['target'] = iris.target\n",
        "df_reference['target_name'] = df_reference['target'].map(\n",
        "    {i: name for i, name in enumerate(iris.target_names)}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"📊 Dataset cargado: {len(df_reference)} muestras\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nPrimeras filas:\")\n",
        "df_reference.head()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 🔄 3. Simulación de Predicciones\n",
        "\n",
        "Enviamos 50 muestras aleatorias al API y registramos las respuestas.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Seleccionar 50 muestras aleatorias\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "sample_indices = np.random.choice(len(df_reference), size=50, replace=False)\n",
        "df_sample = df_reference.iloc[sample_indices].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"🎲 Seleccionadas {len(df_sample)} muestras para predicción\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nDistribución de clases:\")\n",
        "print(df_sample['target_name'].value_counts())\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Enviar predicciones y almacenar resultados\n",
        "results = []\n",
        "errors = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"🚀 Enviando predicciones al API...\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "for idx, row in df_sample.iterrows():\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        # Preparar datos\n",
        "        payload = {\n",
        "            \"sepal_length\": float(row['sepal_length']),\n",
        "            \"sepal_width\": float(row['sepal_width']),\n",
        "            \"petal_length\": float(row['petal_length']),\n",
        "            \"petal_width\": float(row['petal_width'])\n",
        "        }\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Enviar request\n",
        "        response = requests.post(\n",
        "            f\"{IRIS_API_URI}/predict\",\n",
        "            json=payload,\n",
        "            timeout=5\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "            result = response.json()\n",
        "            \n",
        "            # Almacenar resultado\n",
        "            results.append({\n",
        "                'sepal_length': row['sepal_length'],\n",
        "                'sepal_width': row['sepal_width'],\n",
        "                'petal_length': row['petal_length'],\n",
        "                'petal_width': row['petal_width'],\n",
        "                'true_target': row['target'],\n",
        "                'true_label': row['target_name'],\n",
        "                'predicted_target': result['prediction'],\n",
        "                'predicted_label': result['prediction_label'],\n",
        "                'confidence': result['confidence'],\n",
        "                'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat()\n",
        "            })\n",
        "            \n",
        "            if len(results) % 10 == 0:\n",
        "                print(f\"   ✅ {len(results)} predicciones completadas...\")\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            errors += 1\n",
        "            print(f\"   ⚠️  Error {response.status_code} en muestra {idx}\")\n",
        "            \n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        errors += 1\n",
        "        print(f\"   ❌ Excepción en muestra {idx}: {e}\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Pequeña pausa para no saturar el API\n",
        "    time.sleep(0.1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear DataFrame con resultados\n",
        "df_predictions = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n✅ Simulación completada:\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Predicciones exitosas: {len(df_predictions)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Errores: {errors}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Mostrar primeras predicciones\n",
        "print(\"📋 Primeras predicciones:\")\n",
        "df_predictions.head(10)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Calcular accuracy\n",
        "correct = (df_predictions['true_target'] == df_predictions['predicted_target']).sum()\n",
        "total = len(df_predictions)\n",
        "accuracy = correct / total if total > 0 else 0\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"📈 Accuracy de las predicciones: {accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Correctas: {correct}/{total}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Matriz de confusión simple\n",
        "print(f\"\\n📊 Distribución de predicciones:\")\n",
        "print(df_predictions.groupby(['true_label', 'predicted_label']).size().unstack(fill_value=0))\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📈 4. Registro en MLflow\n",
        "\n",
        "Registramos las métricas de esta simulación en MLflow.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Iniciar run de MLflow\n",
        "with mlflow.start_run(run_name=f\"simulation_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}\"):\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Registrar parámetros\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"n_samples\", len(df_predictions))\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"api_uri\", IRIS_API_URI)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"timestamp\", datetime.now().isoformat())\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Registrar métricas\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"accuracy\", accuracy)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"correct_predictions\", correct)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"total_predictions\", total)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"errors\", errors)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Calcular y registrar confianza promedio\n",
        "    avg_confidence = df_predictions['confidence'].mean()\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"avg_confidence\", avg_confidence)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Registrar por clase\n",
        "    for label in df_predictions['predicted_label'].unique():\n",
        "        count = (df_predictions['predicted_label'] == label).sum()\n",
        "        mlflow.log_metric(f\"predictions_{label}\", count)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Guardar DataFrame como artifact\n",
        "    df_predictions.to_csv(\"/tmp/predictions.csv\", index=False)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_artifact(\"/tmp/predictions.csv\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    print(\"✅ Métricas registradas en MLflow\")\n",
        "    print(f\"\\n🔗 Ver resultados en: {MLFLOW_URI}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 🔍 5. Detección de Drift con Evidently\n",
        "\n",
        "Generamos un reporte de Data Quality y Data Drift comparando nuestras predicciones con el dataset de referencia.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Preparar datos para Evidently\n",
        "# Reference: Todo el dataset original\n",
        "df_reference_evidently = df_reference[feature_names].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Current: Las muestras que usamos para predicción\n",
        "df_current_evidently = df_predictions[feature_names].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"📊 Datos preparados para Evidently:\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Reference: {len(df_reference_evidently)} muestras\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Current: {len(df_current_evidently)} muestras\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Crear reporte de Evidently\n",
        "report = Report(metrics=[\n",
        "    DataQualityPreset(),\n",
        "    DataDriftPreset()\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generar reporte\n",
        "report.run(\n",
        "    reference_data=df_reference_evidently,\n",
        "    current_data=df_current_evidently\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Reporte de Evidently generado\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Guardar reporte HTML\n",
        "report_filename = f\"iris_drift_report_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}.html\"\n",
        "report_path = f\"/app/reports/{report_filename}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear directorio si no existe\n",
        "import os\n",
        "os.makedirs(\"/app/reports\", exist_ok=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Guardar\n",
        "report.save_html(report_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Reporte guardado en: {report_path}\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\n💡 Puedes descargarlo desde Jupyter o verlo en el navegador\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Mostrar resumen de drift\n",
        "report_dict = report.as_dict()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"📊 Resumen de Data Drift:\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extraer métricas principales\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    metrics = report_dict.get('metrics', [])\n",
        "    \n",
        "    for metric in metrics:\n",
        "        if 'DatasetDriftMetric' in str(metric.get('metric', '')):\n",
        "            result = metric.get('result', {})\n",
        "            drift_detected = result.get('dataset_drift', False)\n",
        "            n_drifted = result.get('number_of_drifted_columns', 0)\n",
        "            n_columns = result.get('number_of_columns', 0)\n",
        "            drift_share = result.get('share_of_drifted_columns', 0)\n",
        "            \n",
        "            print(f\"   Drift detectado: {'⚠️  SÍ' if drift_detected else '✅ NO'}\")\n",
        "            print(f\"   Columnas con drift: {n_drifted}/{n_columns}\")\n",
        "            print(f\"   Proporción de drift: {drift_share:.2%}\")\n",
        "            \n",
        "            if n_drifted > 0:\n",
        "                drifted_cols = result.get('drift_by_columns', {})\n",
        "                print(f\"\\n   Features con drift:\")\n",
        "                for col, has_drift in drifted_cols.items():\n",
        "                    if has_drift:\n",
        "                        print(f\"      - {col}\")\n",
        "            break\n",
        "            \n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"⚠️  No se pudo extraer resumen de drift: {e}\")\n",
        "    print(\"   Ver reporte completo en el archivo HTML\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ✅ 6. Conclusiones\n",
        "\n",
        "### Resumen de la simulación:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Conectividad**: Todos los servicios (MLflow, Evidently, Iris API) están operativos ✅\n",
        "2. **Predicciones**: Se enviaron 50 muestras al modelo de Iris ✅\n",
        "3. **Monitoreo**: Métricas registradas en MLflow ✅\n",
        "4. **Drift Detection**: Reporte generado con Evidently ✅\n",
        "\n",
        "### Próximos pasos:\n",
        "\n",
        "- 🔗 Revisa el experimento en MLflow: http://localhost:30001\n",
        "- 📊 Abre el reporte de Evidently guardado en `/app/reports/`\n",
        "- 🧪 Experimenta cambiando los datos de entrada para simular drift\n",
        "- 📈 Escala el Iris API a más réplicas: `kubectl scale deployment iris-api --replicas=5`\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🎓 Conceptos Aprendidos\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **DNS de Kubernetes**: Los servicios se comunican por nombres (`http://iris-service:8000`)\n",
        "2. **Alta Disponibilidad**: El Iris API tiene 2 réplicas (load balancing automático)\n",
        "3. **Patrón Inmutable**: El modelo está \"cocinado\" en la imagen Docker\n",
        "4. **Monitoreo MLOps**: MLflow para tracking + Evidently para drift detection\n",
        "5. **IaC con Terraform**: Toda la infraestructura es código versionable\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "¡Felicidades! 🎉 Has completado la simulación de MLOps en Kubernetes.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 🚀 Clase 4 - Simulación de Inferencia y Monitoreo en Kubernetes\n",
        "\n",
        "En este notebook vamos a:\n",
        "1. ✅ Verificar la conectividad con los servicios (Smoke Tests)\n",
        "2. 📊 Simular tráfico de inferencia al modelo Iris\n",
        "3. 📈 Monitorear con Evidently para detectar drift\n",
        "\n",
        "**Importante**: Estamos corriendo dentro del clúster de Kubernetes, por lo que usaremos los nombres DNS internos de los servicios.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import requests\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
        "import json\n",
        "from datetime import datetime\n",
        "import time\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📡 Configuración de Servicios\n",
        "\n",
        "Usamos los nombres DNS internos de Kubernetes:\n",
        "- `mlflow-service:5000` - MLflow Tracking Server\n",
        "- `evidently-service:8000` - Evidently Service\n",
        "- `iris-service:8000` - API de Inferencia\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# URLs de los servicios internos\n",
        "MLFLOW_URL = \"http://mlflow-service:5000\"\n",
        "EVIDENTLY_URL = \"http://evidently-service:8000\"\n",
        "IRIS_API_URL = \"http://iris-service:8000\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"🎯 MLflow URL: {MLFLOW_URL}\")\n",
        "print(f\"🎯 Evidently URL: {EVIDENTLY_URL}\")\n",
        "print(f\"🎯 Iris API URL: {IRIS_API_URL}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 🎯 Simulación de Monitoreo MLOps en Kubernetes\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objetivos\n",
        "1. ✅ Verificar conectividad con los servicios del clúster\n",
        "2. 📊 Simular tráfico de predicción al modelo Iris\n",
        "3. 🔍 Monitorear drift con Evidently\n",
        "4. 📈 Registrar métricas en MLflow\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import requests\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
        "from datetime import datetime\n",
        "import json\n",
        "import mlflow\n",
        "import time\n",
        "from IPython.display import display, Markdown\n",
        "\n",
        "# Configuración de URLs (desde variables de entorno)\n",
        "MLFLOW_URI = os.getenv(\"MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI\", \"http://mlflow-service.mlops.svc.cluster.local:5000\")\n",
        "EVIDENTLY_URL = os.getenv(\"EVIDENTLY_SERVICE_URL\", \"http://evidently-service.mlops.svc.cluster.local:8000\")\n",
        "IRIS_API_URL = os.getenv(\"IRIS_API_URL\", \"http://iris-service.mlops.svc.cluster.local:8000\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Configurar MLflow\n",
        "mlflow.set_tracking_uri(MLFLOW_URI)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Librerías importadas correctamente\")\n",
        "print(f\"📍 MLflow URI: {MLFLOW_URI}\")\n",
        "print(f\"📍 Evidently URL: {EVIDENTLY_URL}\")\n",
        "print(f\"📍 Iris API URL: {IRIS_API_URL}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 1️⃣ Smoke Test: Verificar Conectividad\n",
        "\n",
        "Verificamos que todos los servicios estén disponibles en el clúster.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def check_service(name, url, path=\"/\"):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Verifica que un servicio esté activo\"\"\"\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        response = requests.get(f\"{url}{path}\", timeout=5)\n",
        "        if response.status_code == 200:\n",
        "            print(f\"✅ {name}: OK (Status {response.status_code})\")\n",
        "            return True\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            print(f\"⚠️  {name}: Respuesta {response.status_code}\")\n",
        "            return False\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"❌ {name}: Error - {str(e)}\")\n",
        "        return False\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"🔍 Verificando servicios...\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "services_ok = [\n",
        "    check_service(\"MLflow\", MLFLOW_URI, \"/health\"),\n",
        "    check_service(\"Evidently\", EVIDENTLY_URL, \"/api/version\"),\n",
        "    check_service(\"Iris API\", IRIS_API_URL, \"/health\")\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "if all(services_ok):\n",
        "    display(Markdown(\"### ✅ Todos los servicios están operativos\"))\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    display(Markdown(\"### ⚠️ Algunos servicios no están disponibles\"))\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 2️⃣ Obtener Información del Modelo\n",
        "\n",
        "Consultamos la metadata del modelo desplegado.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Obtener información del modelo\n",
        "response = requests.get(f\"{IRIS_API_URL}/model/info\")\n",
        "model_info = response.json()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"📋 Información del Modelo:\\n\")\n",
        "print(json.dumps(model_info, indent=2))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Guardar features para referencia\n",
        "feature_names = model_info['model']['feature_names']\n",
        "target_names = model_info['model']['target_names']\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 3️⃣ Cargar Dataset de Referencia\n",
        "\n",
        "Cargamos el dataset Iris para simular tráfico de producción.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Cargar dataset Iris\n",
        "iris = load_iris()\n",
        "X = iris.data\n",
        "y = iris.target\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear DataFrame\n",
        "df_reference = pd.DataFrame(X, columns=feature_names)\n",
        "df_reference['target'] = y\n",
        "df_reference['target_name'] = df_reference['target'].map(\n",
        "    {i: name for i, name in enumerate(target_names)}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"📊 Dataset cargado: {len(df_reference)} muestras\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nPrimeras 5 filas:\")\n",
        "display(df_reference.head())\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nDistribución de clases:\")\n",
        "display(df_reference['target_name'].value_counts())\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 4️⃣ Simulación de Tráfico: Enviar Predicciones\n",
        "\n",
        "Enviamos 50 muestras aleatorias al endpoint de predicción.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def send_prediction_request(features):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Envía una solicitud de predicción al servicio Iris\"\"\"\n",
        "    payload = {\n",
        "        \"sepal_length\": float(features[0]),\n",
        "        \"sepal_width\": float(features[1]),\n",
        "        \"petal_length\": float(features[2]),\n",
        "        \"petal_width\": float(features[3])\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    \n",
        "    response = requests.post(f\"{IRIS_API_URL}/predict\", json=payload)\n",
        "    return response.json()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Seleccionar 50 muestras aleatorias\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "sample_indices = np.random.choice(len(df_reference), size=50, replace=False)\n",
        "df_sample = df_reference.iloc[sample_indices].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"🚀 Iniciando simulación de tráfico...\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "predictions = []\n",
        "errors = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "for idx, (i, row) in enumerate(df_sample.iterrows(), 1):\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        features = [row['sepal length (cm)'], row['sepal width (cm)'], \n",
        "                   row['petal length (cm)'], row['petal width (cm)']]\n",
        "        \n",
        "        result = send_prediction_request(features)\n",
        "        predictions.append(result)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if idx % 10 == 0:\n",
        "            print(f\"✅ Enviadas {idx}/50 predicciones...\")\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Pequeña pausa para simular tráfico real\n",
        "        time.sleep(0.1)\n",
        "        \n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"❌ Error en predicción {idx}: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "        errors += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n✅ Simulación completada\")\n",
        "print(f\"   - Total enviadas: {len(predictions)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   - Errores: {errors}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostrar algunas predicciones\n",
        "print(\"\\n📊 Ejemplos de predicciones:\")\n",
        "for i, pred in enumerate(predictions[:3], 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nPredicción {i}:\")\n",
        "    print(f\"  - Clase: {pred['prediction']}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"  - Confianza: {pred['confidence']:.2%}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"  - Probabilidades: {pred['probabilities']}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Extraer predicciones y features\n",
        "df_production = df_sample[feature_names].copy()\n",
        "df_production['prediction'] = [p['prediction'] for p in predictions]\n",
        "df_production['prediction_id'] = [p['prediction_id'] for p in predictions]\n",
        "df_production['confidence'] = [p['confidence'] for p in predictions]\n",
        "df_production['timestamp'] = [p['timestamp'] for p in predictions]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Añadir ground truth\n",
        "df_production['target'] = df_sample['target'].values\n",
        "df_production['target_name'] = df_sample['target_name'].values\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"📊 Datos de producción preparados\")\n",
        "print(f\"   - Muestras: {len(df_production)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nPrimeras 5 predicciones:\")\n",
        "display(df_production[['prediction', 'confidence', 'target_name']].head())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calcular accuracy\n",
        "accuracy = (df_production['prediction'] == df_production['target_name']).mean()\n",
        "print(f\"\\n📈 Accuracy en este batch: {accuracy:.2%}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 6️⃣ Análisis de Drift con Evidently\n",
        "\n",
        "Generamos un reporte de Data Drift comparando datos de referencia vs producción.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from evidently.report import Report\n",
        "from evidently.metric_preset import DataDriftPreset\n",
        "\n",
        "# Usar el 50% del dataset original como referencia\n",
        "df_ref = df_reference.sample(n=75, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"🔍 Generando reporte de Evidently...\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear reporte\n",
        "report = Report(metrics=[DataDriftPreset()])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ejecutar reporte\n",
        "report.run(\n",
        "    reference_data=df_ref[feature_names],\n",
        "    current_data=df_production[feature_names]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Guardar reporte\n",
        "report_path = \"/workspace/notebooks/drift_report.html\"\n",
        "report.save_html(report_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Reporte generado: {report_path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostrar resumen\n",
        "report_dict = report.as_dict()\n",
        "drift_detected = report_dict['metrics'][0]['result']['dataset_drift']\n",
        "\n",
        "if drift_detected:\n",
        "    display(Markdown(\"### ⚠️ DRIFT DETECTADO\"))\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    display(Markdown(\"### ✅ No se detectó drift significativo\"))\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## 7️⃣ Registrar Métricas en MLflow\n",
        "\n",
        "Registramos las métricas de este experimento en MLflow.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Configurar experimento\n",
        "experiment_name = \"iris-production-monitoring\"\n",
        "mlflow.set_experiment(experiment_name)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"📝 Registrando experimento en MLflow: {experiment_name}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "with mlflow.start_run(run_name=f\"simulation_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}\"):\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Parámetros\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"num_predictions\", len(predictions))\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"model_type\", \"RandomForestClassifier\")\n",
        "    mlflow.log_param(\"deployment\", \"kubernetes\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Métricas\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"accuracy\", accuracy)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"avg_confidence\", df_production['confidence'].mean())\n",
        "    mlflow.log_metric(\"drift_detected\", int(drift_detected))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Por clase\n",
        "    for target_name in target_names:\n",
        "        mask = df_production['target_name'] == target_name\n",
        "        class_accuracy = (df_production[mask]['prediction'] == df_production[mask]['target_name']).mean()\n",
        "        mlflow.log_metric(f\"accuracy_{target_name}\", class_accuracy)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Guardar reporte de Evidently como artifact\n",
        "    mlflow.log_artifact(report_path)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Guardar datos de predicción\n",
        "    predictions_path = \"/workspace/notebooks/predictions.csv\"\n",
        "    df_production.to_csv(predictions_path, index=False)\n",
        "    mlflow.log_artifact(predictions_path)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    run_id = mlflow.active_run().info.run_id\n",
        "    print(f\"✅ Experimento registrado con ID: {run_id}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"\\n📊 Métricas registradas:\")\n",
        "    print(f\"   - Accuracy: {accuracy:.2%}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"   - Avg Confidence: {df_production['confidence'].mean():.2%}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"   - Drift Detected: {drift_detected}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "display(Markdown(f\"\"\"\n",
        "### 🎉 Simulación Completada\n",
        "\n",
        "#### 📊 Resultados:\n",
        "- **Predicciones enviadas:** {len(predictions)}\n",
        "- **Accuracy:** {accuracy:.2%}\n",
        "- **Confianza promedio:** {df_production['confidence'].mean():.2%}\n",
        "- **Drift detectado:** {'Sí ⚠️' if drift_detected else 'No ✅'}\n",
        "\n",
        "#### 🔗 Accede a los servicios:\n",
        "\n",
        "**Desde tu navegador (localhost):**\n",
        "- 📈 [MLflow UI](http://localhost:5000)\n",
        "- 🔍 [Evidently Dashboard](http://localhost:8000)\n",
        "- 🌸 [Iris API Docs](http://localhost:9000/docs)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Desde el clúster (DNS interno):**\n",
        "- MLflow: `{MLFLOW_URI}`\n",
        "- Evidently: `{EVIDENTLY_URL}`\n",
        "- Iris API: `{IRIS_API_URL}`\n",
        "\n",
        "#### 📝 Próximos pasos:\n",
        "1. Explora el reporte de drift: `drift_report.html`\n",
        "2. Revisa las métricas en MLflow UI\n",
        "3. Experimenta con diferentes escenarios de drift\n",
        "\"\"\"))\n"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "language_info": {
      "name": "python"
    }
  },
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 2
}
